ks about her career as a midwife and her commitment to ROSA e.V. - Rolling Safespace for refugee women in Greece. Read the article Read more alumni stories Our mission The alumni network is international, interdisciplinary – and constantly growing. The strength of our University of Tübingen is constituted by its people: our alumni, researchers, lecturers, members of staff, friends and supporters from politics and the economy. We are all connected by a shared pride in the University of Tübingen and a deep respect for its tradition and excellence. The Alumni Relations team is here to keep you up to date on the latest news from the University and to show you how you can support your alma mater. Whether you are interested in donating your time, talents or resources: We will show you how you can have a lasting impact on the University of Tübingen. The University of Tübingen: An excellent research institution and a place for meaningful connections and valuable experiences. Contact us Do you have queries or feedback regarding the alumni network? Please contact alumni spam prevention @uni-tuebingen.de Official LinkedIn alumni group Instagram Your Alumni Relations team Dr. Rebecca Hahn, Inga van Gessel, Sandra Zepernick Celebrate Pride Month 2024 With Us! June is Pride Month! The goal is to celebrate the history, culture, and importance of the LGBTQIA+ community at the university and in the city, to address discrimination, provide education, and promote solidarity. We would like to offer a rich program at our university, so I warmly invite you to contribute to Pride Month 2024 by organizing such things as: • Lectures • (Guest) talks • Panel discussions • Film screenings • Networking meetings • Workshops • Exhibitions • Information booths Find out more https://uni-tuebingen.de/en/universitaet/campusleben/veranstaltungen/zentrale-veranstaltungen/pride-month-2024/ Key services Official bulletins Disabled access Advice for international students Media Semester Dates Jobs Organiz