stitution, the University of Tübingen relies on experienced and highly-trained specialists in the field of information technology. With a network of over 6,000 employees, the University offers a technology-based, innovative environment and interesting opportunities for development in the field of IT. Administration As an administrative employee you would make an important contribution to achieving the mission and tasks of the University. Administration provides the services within the University. We need you to support research, teaching and learning with creative, high-quality solutions, and ensure the smooth operation of all processes. Maintenance and technology Are you keen to get the job done? Do you have a passion for technology? Whether in building services, precision or systems engineering, or our many laboratories – the University of Tübingen has numerous opportunities in technology and maintenance. Training From pipetting to programming – if you want a career as a technician, you can find a wide range of training opportunities with us, including biology lab techs, IT specialists or even commercial managers for office management. Learn more University Library With a large number of employees, the University Library offers diverse opportunities and areas of responsibility. Besides being a source of literature and information, the Library runs the University Press and is home to the digital teaching platform and specialist national portals. Work can involve the purchase and licensing of specialist literature and databases, planning training courses and development of IT information systems, etc. Learn more Reasons to work for us We value excellence We live up to our values We foster your career We offer numerous advantages We balance family life and work We love Tübingen backwards scroll forward Key services Official bulletins Disabled access Advice for international students Media Semester Dates Jobs Organizing Your Studies University Library Programs availab