e favorable conditions for women at our university. Gender equality office We offer advice on equal opportunities, we assist with appointment procedures and manage funding measures for women. Learn more Athene program With the Athene program we encourage women on their path to an academic career – with scholarships, mentoring, coaching and networking opportunities. Learn more Good management guidelines Good management and constructive cooperation are the basis for excellent results. With our good management guidelines we are continuing on our path to intensify a culture of cooperation and commitment. Managers should take it in their stride that there are people with very different backgrounds at the university. For me this means: being appreciative and respectful. Vice president Prof. Dr. Monique Scheer Learn more Diversity Diversity is the basis of our excellence. We endeavor to create a diverse university culture, where you can realize your potential regardless of your gender, ethnic origin, age, social or religious background, disability or sexual orientation. Diversity Office The Diversity Office is the first port of call for all issues in relation to diversity. We can advise and support you if you encounter disadvantages and discrimination at work. Learn more The diversity audit We have received the “Vielfalt gestalten” diversity audit certificate from the donors’ association. This recognizes that we are committed to sustainable diversity management for our students and staff. Learn more Sustainability Protecting the climate and the environment concerns all of us. We at the university also play our part and take our responsibility to society and future generations seriously. Climate and environmental protection All our energy is green – from hydropower; we are steadily reducing our consumption of water and paper, and we are optimizing our heating, ventilation and lighting systems. Learn more EMAS Eco-Management and Audit Scheme We were the first Baden-Württemberg university to receive the EMAS certificate, back in 2011. The EU’s environmental management hallmark recognizes our ongoing improvement in environmental performance. Learn more Internationalism The internationalization of our university is important to us. We are networked with research and exchange partners all around the world. Discover our international profile . Networks The University of Tübingen is involved in three international university networks. Matariki The Guild CIVIS Partnerships As a globally networked research university, we have strong relationships with a number of international partner universities. Learn more Reasons to work for us We value excellence We live up to our values We foster your career We offer numerous advantages We balance family life and work We love Tübingen backwards scroll forward Key services Official bulletins Disabled access Advice for international students Media Semester Dates Jobs Organizing Your Studies University Library Programs available Welcome Center for Scholars Further services System status Corporate Design Conference materials Maps Cafeteria menu Newsletter Uni Tübingen aktuell Studium Generale Uni shop Calendar of events Portals ALMA Exchange Mail (OWA) Research information system FIT ILIAS, moodle Search for persons at the University (EPV) Praxisportal Timms Video Portal Webmail Uni Tübingen Contact us University of Tübingen Geschwister-Scholl-Platz 72074 Tübingen Germany Phone: +49 7071 29-0 Contact us Facebook Twitter Youtube Instagram LinkedIn Mastodon © 2024 Eberhard Karls Universität Tübingen, Tübingen Imprint Data Privacy Statement Barrierefreiheit RSS-Feed Shortcut Print	{podcasts,professors,fördermöglichkeiten,datenschutzbeauftragter,teilnahmevoraussetzungen,forschungsschwerpunkte,webmail,hochschulweiterbildung,professorships,universities,doctorates,humanities,biology,academics,semesters,germany,unfallversicherung,teacher,library,studienmodelle,scholarships,isotopenlabor,alums,online,university,weite