ly vibrant regions in Germany. This means that there are good job prospects for your family members, an airport, and the buzz of a big city just around the corner. Learn more Nature Schönbuch nature reserve, the Swabian Alb, the Black Forest. There are nearby forests, meadows and mountains with numerous castles for hikers, mountain bikers and nature lovers. Schönbuch The Swabian Alb The Black Forest BBC TRAVEL Tübingen: Europe’s fiercely vegan, fairy-tale city In Germany's south-west, nestled between the alps of the Swabian region and the densely wooded Schönbuch nature park, lies Tübingen, a university city that would put most Disney locations to shame. Read the article City of knowledge Besides our historic university, the city is home to a number of independent leading research institutes. Learn more Life in Tübingen Relocation, accommodation, local tips: you can find practical information about living in Tübingen on the Tübingen Research Campus website. Learn more Sustainability The City of Tübingen is serious about sustainability. It is an official Fairtrade city, has a first-class network of cycle paths and is a pioneer in the reduction of disposable packaging. Learn more Reasons to work for us We value excellence We live up to our values We foster your career We offer numerous advantages We balance family life and work We love Tübingen backwards scroll forward Key services Official bulletins Disabled access Advice for international students Media Semester Dates Jobs Organizing Your Studies University Library Programs available Welcome Center for Scholars Further services System status Corporate Design Conference materials Maps Cafeteria menu Newsletter Uni Tübingen aktuell Studium Generale Uni shop Calendar of events Portals ALMA Exchange Mail (OWA) Research information system FIT ILIAS, moodle Search for persons at the University (EPV) Praxisportal Timms Video Portal Webmail Uni Tübingen Contact us University of Tübingen Geschwister-Scholl-Platz 72074 Tübing