eginning of the semester, numerous information events are held at the university for first-year students, which make it considerably easier for them to start their studies. The individual institutes also offer introductory events . For further information please refer to their homepages or ask at the respective secretariats. Above all, first-year students are strongly advised to have an individual counselling interview with the respective study advisor before the start of the semester. Contact persons are also the student representatives ( Fachschaften ). During your studies During the entire period of study you can always talk to the respective Study Advisors of the institutes regarding subject-specific matters. If questions relating to examination issues cannot be solved in this way, please contact the Central Examination Office , which, like the Faculty Administration, is located at Keplerstraße 2 on the 2nd floor. In the event of special problems during your studies, examinations or complaints, please contact the Dean of Studies of the Faculty . For a change of subject after the 3rd semester , subject counselling is mandatory. Deans of Studies Deans of Studies Prof. Dr. Sarah Dessì Schmid Prof. Dr. Stefan Morent (Vice Dean of Studies and Digitality) Departmental Deans of Studies Departmental Deans of Studies Dept 1: Prof. Dr. Bernhard Maier Dept 2: Prof. Dr. Heidrun Eichner Dept 3: Prof. Dr. Jan C. Jansen Dept 4: Prof. Dr. Inga Hennecke Dept 5: Prof. Dr. Bernhard Pörksen Academic Affairs - Faculty Academic Affairs - Faculty Uwe Meyerdirks 29 - 77928 Claudia Cernik 29 - 76858 Henriette Slogsnat 29 - 72952 Keplerstraße 2, 72074 Tübingen E-Mail Links Study in Tübingen Advising and Admission of International Students Online Course Catalogue (ALMA-Portal) Key services Official bulletins Disabled access Advice for international students Media Semester Dates Jobs Organizing Your Studies University Library Programs available Welcome Center for Scholars Further services 